text: Winifred Una Margaretta George (born 19 January 1914 in Mordialloc, Victoria, Australia - died 19 March 1988 in Dandenong, Victoria) was an Australian cricket player. George played three tests for the Australia national women's cricket team. George was the sixteenth woman to play Women's Test cricket for Australia. ==References== Category:1914 births Category:1988 deaths Category:Australia women Test cricketers
